data.summary: [PR Newswire] - DENVER, Dec. 16, 2016 /PRNewswire/ -- For 50 days, Apartment Investment and Management Company (Aimco) team members across the country have volunteered for Valuing Our Veterans, serving the men and women who have served our country, and honoring their families. From coast to coast, the Aimco Cares philanthropic program has sponsored more than 60 unique events from building homes for disabled veterans, to assembling care packages for troops overseas, to visiting veterans' nursing homes. Over the last nine years, Aimco has contributed more than $1 million to TAPS to support its comprehensive program of peer support and crisis intervention for military families who are grieving the loss of a loved one in the line of duty. In the last five years, Aimco has donated $620,000 to Project Sanctuary to aid its mission of helping military personnel reunite with their families after duty overseas and addressing the suicide and divorce rates so prevalent among that population.
data.title: Aimco Donates Golf Tournament Proceeds to Support Military Families: Check Presentations Cap a 50-Day Valuing Our Veterans Volunteer Effort
